# EZjobsite — copy to .env and fill in. .env is git-ignored and must stay that way.
#
# Every key below is read by real code. If a key is missing, the thing that needs it
# REFUSES LOUDLY rather than degrading quietly — that is deliberate, and it is why
# this file lists what breaks rather than just what to paste.

# ── Supabase ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dashboard → Project Settings → API.
# The anon key is PUBLIC BY DESIGN. It identifies the project; RLS and the RPC
# grants are what protect the data. It ships in the app bundle and in the no-login
# confirmation page, and that is correct — anon can reach exactly two RPCs and no
# table (verified: every table returns []).
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://<project-ref>.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# ── Supabase Postgres (migrations only; never shipped to a device) ──────────────
# Dashboard → Project Settings → Database → Connection string.
# NOTE: the pooler REQUIRES a tenant-qualified user — `postgres.<project-ref>`,
# not `postgres`. Plain `postgres` fails with
#   "no tenant identifier provided (external_id or sni_hostname required)"
# which reads like a network error and is not.
SUPABASE_DB_HOST=aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com
SUPABASE_DB_PORT=5432
SUPABASE_DB_NAME=postgres
SUPABASE_DB_USER=postgres.<project-ref>
SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=

# ── PowerSync ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Carries the MUTABLE relational rows (projects). It does NOT carry evidence —
# captures/decisions/notes/scope ride owned outboxes, because PowerSync can revert
# its own rows and so cannot be the commitment authority for something mandate #1
# says must never be lost. See ARCHITECTURE ADR-2's 2026-07-17 amendment.
EXPO_PUBLIC_POWERSYNC_URL=https://<instance>.powersync.journeyapps.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_POWERSYNC_DEV_TOKEN=

# ── The no-login confirmation page (REQ-VAL8) ───────────────────────────────────
# WHERE apps/web/confirm.html IS HOSTED. Until this is set, "SEND IT" REFUSES and
# says why — it will not hand a contractor a dead link to give a client.
#
# NOT Supabase Storage: it refuses to serve renderable HTML (verified — the object
# row records text/html, the CDN serves text/plain, and the same upload of a .json
# serves as application/json; it is a deliberate anti-phishing measure). Any static
# host works — it is one file with no build step. Your own domain is worth it: that
# link is the client's first impression of the contractor.
EXPO_PUBLIC_CONFIRM_BASE=

# ── NOT YET USED BY ANY CODE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The five unbuilt requirements need these. Nothing reads them yet; adding a key
# does not make a feature appear.
#
# REQ-PROC1/PROC3/PROC5 + REQ-P4 (transcription, language detection, structuring,
# content-assisted project resolution). The durable job runtime around the model
# call IS built and proven (sql/140_processing_jobs.sql: leased, resumable,
# reason-carrying, tested against a worker dying mid-job). What is missing is the
# worker: claim_job → fetch → complete_step. Small, BECAUSE the runtime exists.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=
#
# REQ-CAP7 (pre-roll buffer) needs no key — it needs a MICROPHONE. This Mac has
# none (system_profiler: one audio device, output only), so voice capture cannot be
# built or tested here at all. A USB mic or a physical iPhone unblocks it.
#
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is deliberately absent. Nothing needs it: the deploy
# script signs in as an owner instead, because the bucket policy already allows it
# and a leaked deploy script must not become full database access.
